PARIS - Former champion Garbine Muguruza made the French Open quarter-finals on Monday when opponent Lesia Tsurenko quit after just two games with a leg injury. Third seed Muguruza, the 2016 champion, was only on court for 20 minutes. #OnThisDay in 2016 Garbine Muguruza beat Serena Williams 7-5, 6-4 to win her first #FrenchOpen title
		
